In JIRA Studio, we've needed to extend the UserPickerBrowser with a custom action that accepts additional request parameters. Unfortunately, the JavaScript code in autocomplete.js that hooks up the click event to the user picker popup trigger does not provide a way to add parameters to the popup window URL. This means we have had to re-implement that code in our UI.

In our case, the value of the parameter is dependent on another form element, so when addressing this issue, please allow for the extra parameters to be defined dynamically when the popup is triggered (rather than only set once when the popup is initialised).

