We're adding JIRA integration to the FindBugs Cloud, a web service for managing and tracking bugs reported by FindBugs. I'd like to allow users to check the status of a JIRA bug corresponding to a FindBugs bug - without having to log into the bug tracker. Users can also create JIRA bugs from FindBugs, which of course requires login, but it seems that we shouldn't need to ask the user to authenticate to access something that would be shown to an unauthenticated user via the normal JIRA webapp.

